    "Finally, for recent results and a comparison of all the type of conditions leading to fast rates in learning theory (including situations with unbounded losses), see Grünwald and Mehta (2020).",
    "Remark 4.2.",
    "All the PAC-Bayes inequalities seen before Section 4 were empirical.",
    "Most of them led to the rate 1/ √ n, except when the empirical error is close to zero, where we obtained the rate 1/n.",
